cial Capital Hedosophia Holdings Corp. VI. The bank=E2=80=99s fee is paid p=
artly up front and partly when the SPAC closes its acquisition.[4] Of cours=
e =E2=80=9Cthe view that blank-check companies democratize finance=E2=80=9D=
 is silly, but I don=E2=80=99t actually believe that it=E2=80=99s commonly =
held. I think it=E2=80=99s just a thing that SPAC sponsors say sometimes, b=
ut that no one believes.=C2=A0[5] The theory I link to, which we discussed =
a couple of weeks ago, is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0very aggressive =E2=80=A6=C2=A0but=
 you could have other theories along the lines of =E2=80=9Cthe SPAC *knew* =
that its projections were false," and I think you will at least sometimes h=
ave something to work with.
